				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Give the tracking one charges (mana batteries recharge), and it might work.  The main problem would be the extra coding to "unlock" the track window for one use when this is used.  If tracking itself was more dynamic (i.e. you didn't have to close the track window and punch the button to refresh the list) a tracking device would be more viable.  
<br />

<br />
The foraging device, however... If it was created, it would have to be unlimited charges and useable by anyone (not just gnomes).  As far as base 'skill' it would replicate, I doubt it would be more than 100.  
<br />

<br />
Perhaps there should be a new skill, "Mechanics", that all races get--the skill that determines whether or not you successfully use a mechanical (i.e. read 'Tinkered') device!  Of course, all gnomes would start out with exceptional skill <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
